               <p>JOHN HASTINGS. I am a <rs id="t18310407-154-viclabel848" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-154-victim1213 t18310407-154-viclabel848"></join>, and live in Vauxhall-bridge-road. On the 4th of April I hired the prisoner as an <rs id="t18310407-154-deflabel849" type="occupation">errand-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-154-defend1211 t18310407-154-deflabel849"></join>, and had his character from his father, who had been an officer in the Penitentiary - I sent him in about an hour after he came in to my employ to purchase half a pound of butter at a neighbour's, and gave him a sovereign to pay for it; he never returned with the butter or sovereign - he was brought to me next day by a boy, who formerly lived with me, and admitted that he had spent the sovereign with some boys at Greenwich fair.</p>
